\section{Takeaways}

\begin{frame}{What to remember}
  \begin{itemize}
    \item Accuracy rises quickly with width, then saturates.
    \item The approximation theorems are existence results -- they do not set
      the width you should train.
    \item The useful capacity is small; measure it, do not assume it.
  \end{itemize}
